{{Infobox person |image= |birth_date=April 12, 1945 |birth_place=New York City |occupation=Film actress }} '''Laura Esterman''' (born April 12, 1945)<ref name=filmr/> is an American actress known for portraying [[Ruby the Galactic Gumshoe]] in contemporary radio dramas and for her [[Drama Desk Award]] and [[Obie Award]] winning performance in the 1992 original stage production of [[Scott McPherson]]'s ''[[Marvin's Room (play)|Marvin's Room]]''.
==Life and career== Esterman was born in New York City, New York, the daughter of Sophie (née Milgram) and Benjamin Esterman, a doctor.<ref name=filmr>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/33/Laura-Esterman.html |title=Laura Esterman Biography (1945-) |publisher=Filmreference.com |date=1945-04-12 |accessdate=2009-05-22}}</ref> She made her [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] debut in the 1969 revival of ''[[The Time of Your Life]]''. Her other Broadway credits include ''[[The Waltz of the Toreadors]]'', ''[[God's Favorite]]'', ''[[Teibele and Her Demon]]'', ''[[The Suicide (play)|The Suicide]]'', ''[[The Metamorphosis|Metamorphosis]]'' and ''[[The Show Off]]''.<ref>{{IBDB name|id=39749}}</ref>
Esterman has also worked in television and film. Her television credits include ''[[Remington Steele]]'', ''[[St. Elsewhere]]'', ''[[The Facts of Life (TV series)|The Facts of Life]]'', ''[[L.A. Law]]'', ''[[Family Ties]]'', ''[[Law & Order]]'', ''[[Third Watch]]'' and ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]'' among others. Her movie credits include ''[[Alone in the Dark (1982 film)|Alone in the Dark]]'', ''[[Ironweed (film)|Ironweed]]'', ''[[Awakenings]]'', ''[[The Doors (film)|The Doors]]'', ''[[Addams Family Values]]'', ''[[The Confession (1999 film)|The Confession]]'' and ''[[Arranged (film)|Arranged]]'' among others.
