'''Nathan George''' is an African-American [[supporting actor]] who was active from 1971-97. He co-won a 1969 [[Obie Award]] with [[Ron O'Neal]] for [[Charles Gordone|Charles Gordone's]] Pulitzer Prize-winning play "No Place to be Somebody."<ref>http://www.infoplease.com/ipa/A0153553.html</ref> This performance also received a [[Drama Desk Award]].<ref>[http://www.ibdb.com/awardperson.asp?id=99060 IBDB Person Awards<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> He acted in ''[[Brubaker]]'' (1980),<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0080474/ Brubaker (1980)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> ''[[Klute]]'' (1971),<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0067309/ Klute (1971)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> ''[[Serpico]]'' (1973),<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0235453/ Harsh Light (1997)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> ''Harsh Light'' (1997), his last film,<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0070666/fullcredits#cast Serpico (1973) - Full cast and crew<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and ''[[One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest (film)|One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest]]'' (1975) and was one of the leads in ''[[Short Eyes]]'' (1977). George currently resides in New York City.

