{{Infobox person | name = Kathleen Maguire | image = Kathleen Maguire East Side West Side 1963.JPG|thumb|Maguire in ''[[East Side/West Side]]''. 1963. | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1925|9|27}} | birth_place = [[New York City, New York]], [[U.S.]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1989|8|9|1925|9|27}} | death_place = New York City, New York, U.S. | death_cause = cancer of the esophagus | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} --> | nationality = | other_names = | ethnicity = <!-- Ethnicity should be supported with a citation from a reliable source --> | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = | years_active = 1949-1986 | known_for = | notable_works = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = }}
'''Kathleen Maguire''' (b. September 27, 1925, New York City, New York — d. August 9, 1989, New York City, New York) was an [[United States|American]] actress who won an [[Obie Award]] in 1958 for her performance in the stage play, ''[[The Time of the Cuckoo]]''. She was also known for two roles in two short lived soap operas on television, first as wealthy widow, Kate Austen on ''[[A Flame in the Wind]]''; and as extremely conservative doctor's wife, Adrian Sims on the series ''[[A World Apart (TV series)|A World Apart]]''. Among her film credits are the 1957 drama [[Edge of the City]] and the 1963 picture [[Flipper (1963 film)|''Flipper'']].
==Death== Maguire died from [[cancer of the esophagus]] on August 9, 1989, at Calvary Hospital, [[The Bronx, New York]]. She was 63 years old and lived in Manhattan. She left no survivors.
==External links== *[http://www.nytimes.com/1989/08/17/obituaries/kathleen-maguire-actress-64.html ''New York Times'' obituary] *{{imdb name|0536594}}
