{{Infobox person | name = Kathryn Grody | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = Kathryn Janis Grody | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1946|11|6|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[Los Angeles, California]], U.S. | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Actress, writer | yearsactive = | spouse = [[Mandy Patinkin]] (1980-present; 2 children) | awards = [[Obie Award]] winner (twice)}}
'''Kathryn Janis Grody''' (born November 6, 1946) is an American actress/writer. After winning two [[Obie Award|Obies]] for her [[off-Broadway]] work, she wrote an autobiographical play called ''A Mom's Life''.<ref name="imdb.com">[http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0342852/bio IMDb profile]</ref>
Grody was born [[Los Angeles, California]]. She has been married to actor/singer [[Mandy Patinkin]] since 1980 and they have two children, Isaac and Gideon. Grody is actor [[Noah Wyle]]'s godmother.<ref name="imdb.com"/>
