'''John Kelly''' is an American [[performance artist]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://theater.nytimes.com/2010/12/13/theater/reviews/13pass.html |title=Egon Schiele Seen From Many Angles |work= [[The New York Times]]|date=12 December 2010|first=Ben|last=Brantley|accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref><ref>[[Roselee Goldberg]] ''Performance Art: From Futurism to the Present'', p. 194, [[Thames & Hudson]], 2001 ISBN 978-0500203392</ref><ref>{{cite news|last = Holden|first = Stephen|title = Review/Performance Art; John Kelly as a Parisian Legend|work = [[The New York Times]]|date = 12 November 1993|url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F0CE1D7173CF931A25752C1A965958260&sec=&spon=&pagewanted=1 |accessdate = 3 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://theater.nytimes.com/mem/theater/treview.html?pagewanted=print&res=940DE6DF133CF936A35757C0A96E948260&scp=43&sq=home%20theater&st=cse |title=Review/Theater; Orpheus Myth in a Whirl Of Song, Dance and Decor |work= [[The New York Times]]|date=5 April 1988|first=Mel|last=Gussow|accessdate=3 September 2012}}</ref><ref>John Kelly ''John Kelly'', [[2wice|2wice Arts Foundation]], 2001 ISBN 0-89381-962-X</ref>
