'''Cynthia Hopkins''' is an American [[performance artist]], [[composer]], and [[musician]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://theater.nytimes.com/2013/02/10/theater/this-clement-world-a-play-about-climate-change.html?pagewanted=all |title=Fate of the Earth Takes Center Stage |work= [[New York Times]]|date=7 February 2013|first=Jason|last=Zinoman|accessdate=11 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://theater.nytimes.com/2013/02/11/theater/reviews/this-clement-world-at-st-anns-warehouse.html |title=An Arctic Awakening With Song and Soul |work= [[New York Times]]|date=10 February 2013|first=Charles|last=Isherwood|accessdate=11 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://brooklynrail.org/2012/05/theater/accordions-in-the-arctic-cynthia-hopkins-sails-ahead |title=ACCORDIONS IN THE ARCTIC: Cynthia Hopkins Sails Ahead |work= The Brooklyn Rail|date=May 2012|first=Michelle|last=Memran|accessdate=27 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/culture/2009/aug/17/accidental-nostalgia-edinburgh-review |title=Accidental Nostalgia |work= [[The Guardian]]|date=17 August 2009|accessdate=27 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://theater.nytimes.com/2010/05/14/theater/reviews/14truth.html?pagewanted=all |title=Excavating What Dad Left Behind |work= [[New York Times]]|date=14 May 2010|first=Ben|last=Brantley|accessdate=27 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2000-05-16/entertainment/18125957_1_lady-macbeth-box-office-ethan-hawke |title=News Beat |work= [[NY Daily News]]|date=16 May 2000|accessdate=16 September 2012}}</ref> She has written, composed, and performed five works of performance art at a number of theaters around the world, including [[St. Ann’s Warehouse]] in Brooklyn, New York and the [[Walker Art Center]] in Minneapolis, Minnesota. She has also self-produced five full-length albums, and is the recipient of a [[Bessie Award]], two [[Obie Award|Obie Awards]], the 2007 [[Alpert Award]] in Theater, and a 2010 [[Guggenheim Fellowship]].
In her work as a performer, Hopkins sings and plays the [[accordion]], [[guitar]], [[piano]], and the [[musical saw]].
