{{Infobox person | name = Adina Porter | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1971|03|13}} | birth_place = [[New York City]], [[United States]] | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Actress | yearsactive = 1992–present }} '''Adina Porter''' is an [[Obie Award|Obie Award-winning]] American actress, known for her recurring role as Lettie Mae Thornton on HBO's ''[[True Blood]]'' and as Kendra on HBO's ''[[The Newsroom (U.S. TV series)|The Newsroom]]''.
Porter's film and TV resume stretches back to 1992's [[Leopold and Loeb|Leopold/Loeb]] [[New Queer Cinema]] feature, ''[[Swoon (film)|Swoon]]'', though she's best known for frequent episodic television guest-starring roles and advertising campaigns for [[GEICO]] and [[Domino's Pizza]]. She played Letecia Barris on the series ''[[Prison Break]]'' and also appeared as Ricky in the film adaptation of Ruben Santiago-Hudson's ''[[Lackawanna Blues]]'' for HBO. Her Broadway debut came in 2001 with the Roundabout Theater's revival of ''[[The Women (play)|The Women]]'', directed by Scott Elliott, broadcast as part of PBS's Stage on Screen series, in addition to many significant off-Broadway and regional theater credits (including her award-winning performance in [[Suzan-Lori Parks|Suzan-Lori Parks's]] 1996 play, ''Venus'') and multiple productions at the New York Shakespeare Festival.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adina Porter|url=http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Adina_Porter&action=edit&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro|work=Lortel archive/Internet off-Broadway Database|accessdate=23 June 2012}}</ref> In 2006, she guest starred in the series ''[[Without a Trace]]'' in an episode called "Watch Over Me" where she plays a social worker. In 2007, she guest starred in the ''[[House (TV series)|House M.D.]]'' episode "[[Family (House)|Family]]". Prior to her work on HBO's hit television series ''[[True Blood]]'' where she plays Lettie Mae Thornton, mother to Rutina Wesley's Tara Thorton, Porter spent two seasons as housekeeper Gwen Walker on NBC's ''[[American Dreams]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=True Blood: Actor Bio: Adina Porter|url=http://www.hbo.com/true-blood/cast-and-crew/index.html#/true-blood/cast-and-crew/lettie-mae-thornton/bio/adina-porter.html|publisher=HBO.com|accessdate=23 June 2012}}</ref> wWas also "Silver" the office worker in the movie "Fluffer" ==References== {{reflist}}
